I move into one of the buildings that make up the ruins.  Inside I see that its a fairly small oval shaped room with no obvious exits other than the one I just came in through.  Along one wall are several indentions that may have once served as shelving.  Near the far end of the room is a sunken area of the floor.

At first, I think the sunken area is simply filled with refuse, but when I step closer I realize that the space is filled with something else instead.

In that space are brown tinted clear orbs, a hundred of them, perhaps more.  The outside looks shriveled and appears to have a leathery texture to them.  When I look at the orbs, I can see that there is something inside of each one of them, some tadpole like creature is shriveled and curled up within.

//Eggs, but they look dried up and dead.//  My eyes scan over the eggs, searching for any clue as to what they might have been.

//Clearly some kind of nest,//  I glance around, getting the sudden sense that I'm being watched, //I should probably get out of here, no since being around if whatever laid them comes back.

