Slipping through the oval opening that leads into one of the strange buildings, I start to look around.

The place is wide open for the most part.  One portion of the floor is sunken, filled with leaves and other refuse that seems to have gathered in the low spot over a great many years.  

//How long?  This place hasn't been abandoned for decades, its been centuries, or longer?//  The sense of //ancient// seems to be as much a part of this place as the building itself.

//That sunken spot, maybe eight foot across and round.  It looks like part of the place rather than damage from neglect.  What purpose could it have possibly served?//

After a few minutes, I realize that there's nothing I can learn from the empty place.

